The '''1989 [[Clemson Tigers]] football team''' represented [[Clemson University]] in the 1989 [[college football]] season. The Tigers were led by head coach [[Danny Ford]], who was serving his final season as head coach at Clemson. The Tigers played their home games in [[Memorial Stadium, Clemson|Memorial Stadium]]. The Tigers finished the 1989 season with a 10-2 record and defeated {{cfb link|year=1989|team=West Virginia Mountaineers|title=West Virginia}} 27-7 in the [[1989 Gator Bowl (December)|1989 Gator Bowl]].
